claims:
Claims 1. A system (1) for detecting and preventing forwarding fraud carried out upon call is forwarded to a number registered in a domestic network (DN) in calls made internationally; comprising - at least one signalling data unit (2) which is essentially in communication with the domestic network (DN); - at least one transferred numbers database (3) which is in communication with the domestic network (DN) and keeps records of numbers switching among mobile operators on the domestic network (DN); - at least one data gathering unit (4) which is essentially in communication with the signalling data unit (2) and the transferred numbers database (3); - at least one interpretation unit (5) which is essentially in communication with the data gathering unit (4) and the end systems (US); - at least one suspicious numbers database (6) which is in communication with the interpretation unit (5); and characterized by - at least one signalling data unit (2) which tracks signals regarding calls established on a mobile communication network and transmits signalling data of these calls to the data gathering unit (4); - at least one data gathering unit (4) which records the call signalling data received from the signalling data unit (2) as input and the operator data received from the transferred numbers database (3) upon associating them with one another; - at least one interpretation unit (5) which receives the data recorded upon being associated with one another by the data gathering unit (4) and detects fraud carried out through call forwarding by performing analysis of these received data and consequently takes necessary pre-determined actions in order to prevent the related numbers and gives notice to the end systems (US) as a result of the analysis; 

 - at least one suspicious numbers database (6) which keeps records of data related to the numbers about the fraud detected by the interpretation unit (5). 2. A system (1) according to Claim 1, characterized by the signalling data unit (2) which determines information about duration of an initiated call and its status of being national or international and status of the calling and called party of being mobile-based by using the signal tracking protocols of the domestic network (DN). 3. A system (1) according to Claim 1 or 2, characterized by the signalling data unit (2) which applies pre-determined filters to signalling data and transmits the said data to the data gathering unit (4). 4. A system (1) according to any of the preceding claims, characterized by the interpretation unit (5) which detects whether a call is initiated to a number belonging to a domestic network (DN) from a number belonging to a foreign network (FN) and the call is terminated within a pre-determined period. 5. A system (1) according to Claim 4, characterized by the interpretation unit (5) which controls whether the number called from the foreign network (FN) receives call from the domestic network (DN) within a pre-determined period after the call is terminated and if it is determined as a result of the control transaction that the said number has received call from the domestic network (DN) within a pre-determined period, queries the call initiating number in the suspicious numbers database (6). 6. A system (1) according to Claim 5, characterized by the interpretation unit (5) which adds the queried number to the suspicious numbers database (6) if 

 it detects that the said call initiating number is not recorded in the suspicious numbers database (6) as a result of the query transaction. 7. A system (1) according to Claim 5, characterized by the interpretation unit (5) which updates the number of the queried number becoming suspicious in the suspicious numbers database (6) if it detects that the said call initiating number is recorded in the suspicious numbers database (6) as a result of the query transaction. 8. A system (1) according to Claim 7, characterized by the interpretation unit (5) which carries out a control transaction in the suspicious numbers database (6) after it updates the number of becoming suspicious, and determines the number -the number of becoming suspicious of which reaches a pre-determined threshold value- as a number registered to the fraud operator (FO). 9. A system (1) according to Claim 8, characterized by the interpretation unit (5) which receives the operator information of the number determined as registered to the fraud operator (FO) from the data gathering unit (4) and gives notice to the end systems (US) by means of any data bus provided by the domestic network (DN). 10. A forwarding fraud detection and prevention method (100) for detecting and preventing forwarding fraud carried out by forwarding call to a number recorded in the domestic network (DN) in international calls; characterized by steps of - the signalling data unit (2) tracking the signalling data related to the calls made on the network by using the signal tracking protocols of the domestic network (DN) (101); 

 - the signalling data unit (2) transmitting the information about time, duration of calls made on domestic network (DN) and their status of being national or international and status of the calling and called party of being mobile-based to the data gathering unit (4) together with the information of calling and called party number (102); - the data gathering unit (4) receiving the operator information of the calling numbers from the transferred numbers database (3) (103); - the data gathering unit (4) associating the signalling data and the operator data (104); - the interpretation unit (5) receiving the signalling data and the data associated with the operator information from the data gathering unit (4) (105); - the interpretation unit (5) controlling whether the call initiated from the foreign network (FN) is terminated within a pre-determined period (106); - if it is determined as a result of the control transaction (106) that the call initiated from the foreign network (FN) is not terminated within a predetermined period, the interpretation unit (5) taking no action; - if it is determined as a result of the control transaction (106) that the call initiated from the foreign network (FN) is terminated within a pre- determined period, the interpretation unit (5) controlling whether the called party in the said call has received call from the domestic network (DN) within a pre-determined period (107); - if it is determined as a result of the control transaction (107) that the called party has not received call from the domestic network (DN) within a pre-determined period, the interpretation unit (5) taking no action; - if it is determined as a result of the control transaction (107) that the called party has received call from the domestic network (DN) within a pre-determined period, the interpretation unit (5) controlling whether the number initiating the call is registered in the suspicious numbers database (6) (108); 

 - if it is determined as a result of the control transaction (108) that the party initiating the call from the domestic network (DN) is not registered in the suspicious numbers database (6), the interpretation unit (5) recording the said number to the suspicious numbers database (6) (109); - if it is determined as a result of the control transaction (108) that the party initiating the call from the domestic network (DN) is recorded in the suspicious numbers database (6), the interpretation unit (5) recording the said number to the suspicious numbers database (6) (109) updating the number of becoming suspicious of the party initiating the call in the suspicious numbers database (6) (110); - the interpretation unit (5) controlling the number of becoming suspicious of the party initiating the call recorded in the suspicious numbers database (6) (111); - if it is detected as a result of the control transaction (111) that the number of becoming suspicious of the party initiating the call reaches a predetermined threshold value, the interpretation unit (5) marking the suspicious number as belonging to the fraud operator (FO) and giving notification to the end systems (US) (112); - if it is detected as a result of the control transaction (111) that the number of becoming suspicious of the party initiating the call does not reach a predetermined threshold value, the interpretation unit (5) taking no action. 11. A forwarding fraud detection and prevention method (100) according to Claim 10, characterized by the step of the numbers determined as belonging to the fraud operator (FO) are notified to the related units of the operators where the said numbers are recorded by means of any data bus provided by the domestic network (DN) (112).
